This paper is about a recommendation system that uses neural networks and personalized attention to learn representations of users and items from reviews. The paper focuses on improving the performance of neural recommendation, which is a subfield of information retrieval (cs.IR). The use of natural language processing techniques such as review encoding and attention models suggests that this paper could also be relevant to subfields such as computational linguistics (cs.CL) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the use of neural networks and personalized attention is a common approach in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and computer vision (cs.CV), which are also likely subcategories for this paper.
